events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Charlotte Hornets

headlines.description: — Jonas Valanciunas had 30 points and 17 rebounds and the New Orleans Pelicans spoiled the Charlotte Hornets’ home opener with a wire-to-wire 124-112 victory Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Valanciunas has big night, helps Pelicans beat Hornets

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — San Antonio struggled when Indiana turned up the pressure late.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs hold off final-minute flurry to beat Pacers 137-134

headlines.description: — In his first home game since signing a massive contract to stay in Washington, Bradley Beal was patient most of the night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Beal's late bank shot gives Wizards 102-100 win over Chicago

headlines.description: — Trae Young overcame a scoreless first half to finish with 25 points and 13 assists, John Collins added 23 points and 13 rebounds, and the Atlanta Hawks beat the Orlando Magic 108-98 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young, Collins power Hawks past Magic 108-98

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant broke a tie with a 3-pointer with 56 seconds left and had 27 points to help the Brooklyn Nets beat the Toronto Raptors 109-105 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant breaks late tie with 3, Nets top Raptors 109-105

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum and the Boston Celtics keep on enjoying their trips to Miami.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum and Brown combine for 57, Celtics top Heat 111-104

events.name: Detroit Pistons at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Maybe someday Jalen Brunson can look back and savor the roars from a sold-out crowd that officially welcomed him to Madison Square Garden.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks rout Pistons 130-106 in Brunson's home debut at MSG

headlines.description: — Ja Morant scored 49 points and hit five 3-pointers to lead the Memphis Grizzlies to a 129-122 victory over the Houston Rockets on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ja Morant scores 49 points, Grizzlies beat Rockets 129-122

headlines.description: — Rudy Gobert grabbed the pass from Karl-Anthony Towns in the paint and soared to a wide-open basket for what would've given Minnesota the tying dunk with 34 seconds left in overtime.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz rally to beat Wolves 132-126 in OT reunion with Gobert

events.name: Denver Nuggets at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Nuggets coach Michael Malone so appreciates Nikola Jokic taking over a game and leading the way on both ends.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nikola Jokic notches triple-double as Nuggets top Warriors

events.name: Phoenix Suns at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard scored 41 points and the Portland Trail Blazers beat the Phoenix Suns 113-111 in overtime Friday night for their second straight victory to open the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard has 41 points Trail Blazers beat Suns 113-111 in OT
